II.

Pliny misses Regulus at court. Regulus’ peculiarities when pleading. Pliny deplores the tendency to shorten the time allotted to lawyers,

and praises Regulus' practice in this respect.

O. PLINIUS ARRIANO SUO S.

Illud ipsum, quod oculum modo dextrum modo sinistrum circumlinebat, dextrum, si a petitore, alterum, si a possessore esset acturus, quod candidum splenium in hoc aut in illud supercilium transferebat, quod semper haruspices oon- sulebat de actionis eventu, a nimia superstitione, sed tamen et a magno studiorum honore veniebat.
